Goal: Reduce file resolution

Steps

  1. Read a tiff file 2
  2. Convert read to matrix
  3. Decompose the matrix
  4. Reconstruct the matrix with lower bits
  5. Display images

1. Preprosessing Data, Biosystems Data Analysis, 2022, University of Amsterdam↩

2. File retrieved from: https://people.math.sc.edu/Burkardt/data/tif/tif.html↩

1. Read a tiff file

2. Convert read to matrix 

library("tiff")

i_img <- readTIFF('mountain.tif', native = FALSE, all = FALSE, convert = FALSE, info = FALSE, indexed = FALSE, as.is = FALSE)

3. Decompose the matrix 

USV <-svd(i_img)

4. Reconstruct the matrix with lower bits 

N <- 8
o_img <- USV$u[,1:N] %*% diag(USV$d[1:N]) %*% t(USV$v[,1:N])

# a tif file should have value between 0 and 1 
o_img[o_img<0] <-0
o_img[o_img>1] <-1

5. Display images

Before manipulation 

grid::grid.raster(i_img)

After manipulation 

grid::grid.raster(o_img)
